This paper deals with the challenges of training machine learning models in hardware, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The use of dimensionality reduction models in image classification and speech recognition suggests that this paper could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). However, the focus on hardware implementation and optimization suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the use of machine learning models in general suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
